<span id="freeTextContainer5554064535071570085">The Book of Lost Souls- Michele Muto<br/><br/>Hands down The Book of Lost Souls is the best independently published e-book I have ever had the pleasure of reading. Often readers think that indie books mean they weren’t good enough for a publishing house, but The Book of Lost Souls destroys that theory. With interesting characters, a formidable plot, and good writing, Muto’s book is sure to win a strong following in the YA community. In the end, it reminded me a bit of Heather Brewer’s Chronicle of Vladami</span>
  <span id="freeText5554064535071570085" style="display:none">The Book of Lost Souls- Michele Muto<br /><br />Hands down The Book of Lost Souls is the best independently published e-book I have ever had the pleasure of reading. Often readers think that indie books mean they weren’t good enough for a publishing house, but The Book of Lost Souls destroys that theory. With interesting characters, a formidable plot, and good writing, Muto’s book is sure to win a strong following in the YA community. In the end, it reminded me a bit of Heather Brewer’s Chronicle of Vladamir Tod, an enviable comparison to be sure. In addition, it’s low price point makes this e-book a STEAL!<br /><br />Overall: A-</span>
