        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1905350079" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4058279906198858333"><strong>A YA novel any age will enjoy</strong><br/><br/>I loved this book!I particularly liked Devlin, the Beezelpup, and the antics throughout the book caused by Ivy changing her friend&apos;s pet lizard Spike into a human so she would have a date to the <br/>prom. The running gags with Spike the boy doing decidedly lizard-like things, such as eating bugs, are funny. I REALLY like Michelle Mutos books for adults, so I was sure I would enjoy this one also, and I was not disappointed at all.<br/></span>
  <span id="freeText4058279906198858333" style="display:none"><strong>A YA novel any age will enjoy</strong><br /><br />I loved this book!I particularly liked Devlin, the Beezelpup, and the antics throughout the book caused by Ivy changing her friend's pet lizard Spike into a human so she would have a date to the <br />prom. The running gags with Spike the boy doing decidedly lizard-like things, such as eating bugs, are funny. I REALLY like Michelle Mutos books for adults, so I was sure I would enjoy this one also, and I was not disappointed at all.<br /></span>
